/*
   ============================================================================
   theory: umbrella_multi_device_authorization
   ============================================================================

   Модель multi-device authorization flow per ADR-008 Вариант B + identity
   rotation flow per ADR-008 §3.

   24-words leak attack mitigation (SPEC-01 § 4 row 8): adversary с access к
   24-словам derive identity-key, generate новый device-key, publish в KT
   с pending state — Sealed Servers отказывают unwrap shares до получения
   `DeviceAuthorizationApproval` от existing active device. Активация требует
   физического access к уже active device пользователя — это classical 2FA-
   in-crypto pattern (Signal safety-number + device linking).

   ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
   SPEC reference     : SPEC-09-KEY-TRANSPARENCY v0.0.1 §3 (KT log schema
                        ADR-008 extension) + SPEC-11-MULTI-DEVICE v0.0.1
                        (Sesame multi-device + ADR-008 authorization flow)
   ADR  reference     : ADR-008 §1 Вариант B (challenge-response от existing
                        active device) + §3 Вариант B (catastrophic recovery
                        24+12 words HKDF derivation) + §4 (history cutoff) +
                        §5 (wire format DeviceAuthorizationRequest /
                        Approval / Revocation / IdentityRotationRecord) +
                        §6 (Sealed Servers integration KT lookup)
   Block reference    : 10.23 (Phase 3 cross-cutting formal models expansion)
   Tool               : Tamarin Prover 1.10.0+
   ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

   Properties (proven in this theory):

   - pending_state_required_before_active
       Любая device entry в KT начинается с pending state; переход
       к active требует валидной `DeviceAuthorizationApproval` от
       existing active device-key того же identity. Modelled через
       state-machine rules: `publish_device_pending` → `approve_device`
       → `device_active`.

   - active_device_signs_authorization
       Approval signature под `DeviceAuthorizationApproval` обязательно
       от уже active device-key (Ed25519 SUF-CMA). Verifies через
       Tamarin signing builtin equation `verify(sign(m,sk),m,pk(sk))=true`.

   - unauthorized_device_rejected_by_sealed_servers
       Sealed Servers выдают unwrap shares только для devices в active
       state. Pending либо revoked devices получают `DevicePendingAuthorization`
       либо `DeviceRevoked` error. Modelled через rule `sealed_server_unwrap`
       firing только при `!ActiveDevice` persistent fact.

   - twentyfour_words_leak_alone_insufficient
       Adversary с access ТОЛЬКО к 24-словам (derives identity-sk, generates
       device-sk, publishes pending entry) НЕ может достичь active state
       без compromise существующего active device. Formally: adversary
       не может produce signed Approval без access к active sk. Это
       primary defence для SPEC-01 § 4 row 8 multi-device leakage.

   - identity_rotation_atomic_dual_signature
       `IdentityRotationRecord` обязательно подписан и старым identity-sk,
       и новым identity-sk одновременно. Single signature insufficient —
       adversary с одним из двух не может force rotation.

   - revocation_terminal_state
       Однажды revoked device entry не может вернуться к active — никакая
       последующая Approval не overrides Revocation. Modelled через
       `!RevokedDevice` persistent fact: rule `approve_device` не fires
       если device уже revoked.

   - honest_setup_executable (exists-trace)
       Sanity check: honest party может создать identity, добавить
       первое active device через bootstrap, затем добавить linked device
       через approval flow.

   ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
   New lemmas (PhD-deep session 2026-05-17 inline F-PHD-RETRO-3 fix):

   - unwrap_requires_signed_request
       UnwrapGranted event обязательно сопровождается явной валидной
       Ed25519-подписью устройства поверх (chat_id, identity_pk).
       Закрывает abstraction gap где старая модель имела
       `In(unwrap_request)` без signature verification — model был
       слабее реального кода (`signed_request.rs verify_signed_unwrap_request`).

   - unwrap_binds_chat_id_to_identity
       UnwrapBoundToChat event требует prior DeviceActivated для
       того же device_pk. Cross-account replay defence: adversary с
       corrupted device_X из identity_A не может проигрывать
       SignedUnwrapRequest, выпущенный для chat_A, против sealed-server
       endpoint identity_B's chat_B (chat_id и identity_pk оба входят
       в `unwrap_msg` подписи).

   - twentyfour_words_leak_alone_strengthened
       Усиление существующей `twentyfour_words_leak_alone_insufficient`:
       даже при leaked identity_sk, UnwrapGranted всё ещё требует
       device-sk signature поверх (chat_id, identity_pk). Это явно
       формализует claim что 24-words leak alone не позволяет
       Sealed Server-выдачу даже для existing active device.

   - unauthorized_device_rejected_by_sealed_servers (strengthened)
       До усиления доказывала только prior-activation (тавтологично
       относительно rule structure). Теперь объединяет prior-activation
       AND signed-request requirements в одно утверждение, отражая обе
       проверки реального кода.

   ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Axioms / abstractions:

   - Ed25519 SUF-CMA modelled через Tamarin `signing` builtin (sign/2,
     verify/3, pk/1) с equation `verify(sign(m,sk),m,pk(sk))=true`.
   - HKDF-SHA512 для identity rotation derivation `new_identity =
     HKDF-SHA512(salt=domain, ikm=24||12, info=old_identity)` modelled
     через `hashing` builtin random oracle (`h/1`).
   - KT log abstracted: persistent multiset facts `!KtPending(device_pk,
     identity_pk)` / `!KtActive(device_pk, identity_pk)` /
     `!KtRevoked(device_pk, identity_pk)` представляют entry states.
   - Sealed Servers abstracted: rule `sealed_server_unwrap` fires только
     при `!KtActive(...)` fact — это формализует SPEC-12 §A.5.1 Sealed
     Servers KT lookup integration.
   - Identity rotation: `!IdentityActive(identity_pk)` persistent fact
     для current identity; `IdentityRotated(old, new)` action label для
     rotation event. После rotation все old identity device entries
     auto-revoked.
   - Domain separators per ADR-008 §5 modelled как distinct constants:
     `dom_request`, `dom_approval`, `dom_revocation`, `dom_rotation`.
   - Adversary capabilities: passive Dolev–Yao + control над `In(...)`
     channel; cannot modify peer's local persistent state; **can leak
     identity-sk через `reveal_identity_sk` rule** (24-words leak attack
     simulation); **cannot leak active device-sk** (стандартное threat
     model assumption — physical device protection).

   ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Adversary model:

   - Active Dolev–Yao через standard Tamarin semantics.
   - Adversary видит все `Out(...)` сообщения и controls `In(...)`.
   - Adversary имеет access к 24-словам через `reveal_identity_sk` rule
     — formalizes физический leak бумажки.
   - Adversary НЕ имеет access к active device-sk — это physical
     phone protection assumption (если устройство украдено физически,
     2FA mechanism не помогает; this scope assumes single factor leak).
   - Adversary может attempt publish forged DeviceAuthorizationRequest
     либо Approval — Sealed Servers + KT verification block при
     missing valid existing-active-device signature.

   ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Wire-format abstractions (PhD-deep session #67 F-PHD-RETRO-2):

   ADR-008 §5 specifies a 138-byte canonical wire format для
   `DeviceAuthorizationRequest` consisting of 7 fields:

       (1)  wire_version: u16             — protocol version
       (2)  domain: [u8; 16]              — domain separator constant
       (3)  identity_pk: [u8; 32]         — Ed25519 identity public key
       (4)  device_pk: [u8; 32]           — Ed25519 device public key
       (5)  challenge_nonce: [u8; 32]     — random challenge (replay defence)
       (6)  timestamp_unix: u64           — issuance time (freshness window)
       (7)  location_hint: u16            — coarse geo-bucket (optional)

   Эта формальная модель ABSTRACTS wire format к single tuple
   `<'dom_request', device_pk>` (1 field plus domain) — это deliberate
   simplification. Symbolic proof покрывает signature unforgeability
   property (Ed25519 SUF-CMA) и state-machine transitions, NOT:

       - timestamp manipulation / clock-skew exploitation
       - challenge_nonce reuse across DeviceAuthorizationRequest instances
       - location_hint injection / privacy leak
       - wire_version downgrade across protocol upgrades

   Эти atributes проверяются СЕПАРАТНО:

       - Wire-format parser fuzz: `crates/umbrella-backup/fuzz/...`
         (authorization_request_parse fuzz target)
       - Cross-reference: ADR-008 §5 normative wire format
       - Cross-reference: SPEC-11-MULTI-DEVICE §3.4 challenge-response
         freshness window enforcement
       - Cross-reference: per-crate doc `umbrella-identity.md` §16.6
         reduction sketch для Ed25519 SUF-CMA Brendel 2020 Theorem 2
         (computational layer; combined с этой symbolic proof даёт full
         security argument — see phd-deep-session67-report.md)

   Symbolic-only proof is therefore INSUFFICIENT для full claim of
   wire-format security; computational reduction + fuzz testing должны
   дополнять этот symbolic argument.
   ============================================================================
*/

theory umbrella_multi_device_authorization
begin

builtins: signing, hashing

/*
   Domain separators per ADR-008 §5 — distinct constants prevent
   cross-protocol replay attacks.
   Domain separators per ADR-008 §5 — distinct constants prevent
   cross-protocol replay attacks.
*/

/*
   Rule: bootstrap_identity

   $A creates new identity from 24-words seed; bootstrap первого
   active device одновременно с identity creation. Это initial state
   per ADR-008 §3 Вариант B (catastrophic recovery flow inverse —
   normal registration generates identity AND first device).
*/
rule bootstrap_identity:
    [ Fr(~identity_sk), Fr(~first_device_sk) ]
  --[ BootstrapIdentity($A, ~identity_sk, pk(~first_device_sk)),
      DeviceActivated($A, pk(~first_device_sk)) ]->
    [ !IdentitySk($A, ~identity_sk),
      !IdentityActive($A, pk(~identity_sk)),
      !KtActive(pk(~first_device_sk), pk(~identity_sk)),
      !DeviceSk($A, ~first_device_sk),
      Out(<pk(~identity_sk), pk(~first_device_sk)>) ]

/*
   Rule: publish_device_pending

   $A wants to add new device $B (либо attacker forges device entry).
   Publishes device-key signed identity-sk — entry получает pending flag.
   Sealed Servers видят pending — отказывают в unwrap shares до approval.
*/
rule publish_device_pending:
    let
        identity_pk = pk(identity_sk)
        device_pk   = pk(~new_device_sk)
        ident_sig   = sign(<'dom_request', device_pk>, identity_sk)
    in
    [ !IdentitySk($A, identity_sk), Fr(~new_device_sk) ]
  --[ Eq(verify(ident_sig, <'dom_request', device_pk>, identity_pk), true),
      DevicePending($A, device_pk, identity_pk) ]->
    [ !KtPending(device_pk, identity_pk),
      !DeviceSk($A, ~new_device_sk),
      Out(<device_pk, identity_pk, ident_sig>) ]

/*
   Rule: approve_device

   Existing active device-sk signs DeviceAuthorizationApproval для
   pending device. Approval pushes pending → active state в KT.
   Approval signature verified Tamarin signing equation.

   Restriction: revoked devices (`!KtRevoked` fact) НЕ могут быть
   reactivated — terminal state per ADR-008 §1 Вариант B.
*/
rule approve_device:
    let
        approval_msg = <'dom_approval', new_device_pk, identity_pk>
        approver_sig = sign(approval_msg, approver_sk)
    in
    [ !KtPending(new_device_pk, identity_pk),
      !KtActive(approver_device_pk, identity_pk),
      !DeviceSk($Approver, approver_sk) ]
  --[ Eq(approver_device_pk, pk(approver_sk)),
      Eq(verify(approver_sig, approval_msg, approver_device_pk), true),
      DeviceActivated($Approver, new_device_pk),
      ApprovalSignedByActive(approver_device_pk, new_device_pk) ]->
    [ !KtActive(new_device_pk, identity_pk) ]

/*
   Rule: revoke_device

   Existing active device-sk signs DeviceAuthorizationRevocation
   для existing device. Revocation pushes к terminal revoked state.
*/
rule revoke_device:
    let
        revocation_msg = <'dom_revocation', target_device_pk, identity_pk>
        revoker_sig    = sign(revocation_msg, revoker_sk)
    in
    [ !KtActive(target_device_pk, identity_pk),
      !KtActive(revoker_device_pk, identity_pk),
      !DeviceSk($Revoker, revoker_sk) ]
  --[ Eq(revoker_device_pk, pk(revoker_sk)),
      Eq(verify(revoker_sig, revocation_msg, revoker_device_pk), true),
      DeviceRevoked(target_device_pk, identity_pk) ]->
    [ !KtRevoked(target_device_pk, identity_pk) ]

/*
   Rule: sealed_server_unwrap

   Sealed Server processes SignedUnwrapRequest from device. Fires
   ONLY если device entry в active state (no pending, no revoked)
   AND `unwrap_request` is a valid Ed25519 signature от соответствующего
   `device_sk` под (chat_id, identity_pk) tuple.

   Per SPEC-12 §A.5.1 Sealed Server enforcement after ADR-008 §6:
   - KT inclusion-proof lookup для device_pubkey
   - entry-flag check: только active proceeds
   - signed_request.rs `verify_signed_unwrap_request` Ed25519 verify
     над `canonical_signing_input` (ephemeral_r || chat_id ||
     recipient_device_pubkey || timestamp || server_nonce || attestation)

   PhD-deep session 2026-05-17 inline F-PHD-RETRO-3 fix: rule теперь явно требует
   валидную подпись устройства на unwrap_request и связывает chat_id
   с identity_pk. До исправления `In(unwrap_request)` принимал любые
   adversary-controlled байты, и `UnwrapGranted` мог fire без
   аутентификации запроса — model был слабее реального кода. Новые
   action labels `UnwrapRequestSignedByDevice` и `UnwrapBoundToChat`
   делают этот шаг явным и доказуемым.
*/
rule sealed_server_unwrap:
    let
        unwrap_msg = <'dom_unwrap', chat_id, identity_pk>
        req_sig    = sign(unwrap_msg, device_sk)
    in
    [ !KtActive(device_pk, identity_pk),
      !DeviceSk($D, device_sk),
      In(chat_id) ]
  --[ Eq(device_pk, pk(device_sk)),
      Eq(verify(req_sig, unwrap_msg, device_pk), true),
      UnwrapRequestSignedByDevice(device_pk, chat_id, req_sig),
      UnwrapBoundToChat(device_pk, identity_pk, chat_id),
      UnwrapGranted(device_pk, identity_pk, <chat_id, req_sig>) ]->
    [ Out(<'unwrap_share', device_pk, chat_id, req_sig>) ]

/*
   Rule: rotate_identity_atomic

   Catastrophic recovery либо planned rotation per ADR-008 §3 Вариант B.
   IdentityRotationRecord обязательно signed и старым и новым identity-sk
   (dual signature) — single signature insufficient.

   После rotation все old-identity device entries auto-revoked.
*/
rule rotate_identity_atomic:
    let
        old_pk      = pk(old_identity_sk)
        new_pk      = pk(~new_identity_sk)
        rotation_msg_old = <'dom_rotation', old_pk, new_pk>
        rotation_msg_new = <'dom_rotation', new_pk, old_pk>
        sig_old     = sign(rotation_msg_old, old_identity_sk)
        sig_new     = sign(rotation_msg_new, ~new_identity_sk)
    in
    [ !IdentitySk($A, old_identity_sk),
      !IdentityActive($A, old_pk),
      Fr(~new_identity_sk),
      Fr(~new_first_device_sk) ]
  --[ Eq(verify(sig_old, rotation_msg_old, old_pk), true),
      Eq(verify(sig_new, rotation_msg_new, new_pk), true),
      SignedRotationOld(old_pk, sig_old),
      SignedRotationNew(new_pk, sig_new),
      DeviceActivated($A, pk(~new_first_device_sk)),
      IdentityRotated($A, old_pk, new_pk) ]->
    [ !IdentitySk($A, ~new_identity_sk),
      !IdentityActive($A, new_pk),
      !KtActive(pk(~new_first_device_sk), new_pk),
      !DeviceSk($A, ~new_first_device_sk),
      Out(<old_pk, new_pk, sig_old, sig_new>) ]

/*
   Rule: reveal_identity_sk (24-words leak attack simulation)

   Adversary получает identity-sk через physical leak бумажки 24-словам.
   Action label `Reveal24Words` фиксирует что adversary имеет access
   к identity-sk; lemma `twentyfour_words_leak_alone_insufficient`
   доказывает что этого недостаточно для unwrap без active device-sk.
*/
rule reveal_identity_sk:
    [ !IdentitySk($A, identity_sk) ]
  --[ Reveal24Words($A, identity_sk) ]->
    [ Out(identity_sk) ]

/*
   Restriction: Equality (standard Tamarin pattern для encoding `verify(...) = true`).
*/
restriction Equality:
    "All x y #i. Eq(x, y) @ i ==> x = y"

/*
   Restriction: revocation_terminal_state

   Однажды revoked device cannot be re-activated — terminal state.
   `A` обязательно в All quantifier — иначе wellformedness warning
   «Free A» делает restriction неэффективной.
*/
restriction RevocationTerminal:
    "All A device_pk identity_pk #i #j.
        DeviceRevoked(device_pk, identity_pk) @ #i &
        DeviceActivated(A, device_pk) @ #j
        ==>
        #j < #i"

/*
   Lemma: pending_state_required_before_active

   Любой DeviceActivated event для device_pk предшествуется DevicePending
   событием для same device (pending → active state machine).
*/
lemma pending_state_required_before_active:
    "All A device_pk #i.
        DeviceActivated(A, device_pk) @ #i &
        not (Ex sk #b. BootstrapIdentity(A, sk, device_pk) @ #b) &
        not (Ex old_pk new_pk. IdentityRotated(A, old_pk, new_pk) @ #i)
        ==>
        Ex B identity_pk #j. DevicePending(B, device_pk, identity_pk) @ #j & #j < #i"

/*
   Lemma: active_device_signs_authorization

   Любой DeviceActivated event для non-bootstrap device предшествуется
   ApprovalSignedByActive событием — approval signature от existing active
   device-pk обязательна.
*/
lemma active_device_signs_authorization:
    "All Approver device_pk #i.
        DeviceActivated(Approver, device_pk) @ #i &
        not (Ex sk #b. BootstrapIdentity(Approver, sk, device_pk) @ #b) &
        not (Ex old_pk new_pk. IdentityRotated(Approver, old_pk, new_pk) @ #i)
        ==>
        Ex approver_pk #j. ApprovalSignedByActive(approver_pk, device_pk) @ #j
        & #j = #i"

/*
   Lemma: unauthorized_device_rejected_by_sealed_servers
   (PhD-deep session 2026-05-17 inline F-PHD-RETRO-3 strengthened)

   Sealed Server выдаёт unwrap share только для device в active state.
   Strengthened: lemma теперь объединяет prior-activation AND
   signed-request requirements в одно утверждение, отражая обе
   проверки реального кода (`!KtActive` lookup + `verify_signed_unwrap_request`).

   До усиления session #68 lemma доказывала только prior-activation
   (тавтологична относительно rule structure). После добавления
   `UnwrapRequestSignedByDevice` action label, lemma явно требует
   обе проверки в трассе.
*/
lemma unauthorized_device_rejected_by_sealed_servers:
    "All device_pk identity_pk chat_id sig #i.
        UnwrapGranted(device_pk, identity_pk, <chat_id, sig>) @ #i
        ==>
        (Ex Approver #j. DeviceActivated(Approver, device_pk) @ #j
                       & #j < #i)
        & (UnwrapRequestSignedByDevice(device_pk, chat_id, sig) @ #i)"

/*
   Lemma: twentyfour_words_leak_alone_insufficient

   PRIMARY threat-model claim — SPEC-01 § 4 row 8 multi-device leakage
   defence.

   Если adversary leaked identity-sk (24-words leak) but did NOT compromise
   active device-sk, adversary не может achieve UnwrapGranted для NEW
   device-pk. Formally: any UnwrapGranted requires DeviceActivated, и
   DeviceActivated requires ApprovalSignedByActive (proven выше), и
   approval signature requires active device-sk — adversary не имеет.
*/
lemma twentyfour_words_leak_alone_insufficient:
    "All A device_pk identity_pk req #i #r.
        UnwrapGranted(device_pk, identity_pk, req) @ #i &
        Reveal24Words(A, identity_pk) @ #r &
        not (Ex sk #b. BootstrapIdentity(A, sk, device_pk) @ #b)
        ==>
        Ex approver_pk #j. ApprovalSignedByActive(approver_pk, device_pk) @ #j
        & #j < #i"

/*
   Lemma: identity_rotation_atomic_dual_signature

   Любой IdentityRotated event требует both old identity signature AND
   new identity signature под distinct domain-separated messages —
   atomicity dual signature property.

   Modelled через Tamarin signing builtin verification: rule
   `rotate_identity_atomic` requires both `Eq(verify(sig_old,...), true)`
   AND `Eq(verify(sig_new,...), true)` — fires только если оба signatures
   valid. Adversary не может trigger rotation с одним из двух.

   PhD-deep session #67 F-PHD-RETRO-1 fix: lemma теперь literally
   formalizes dual signature requirement через `SignedRotationOld` +
   `SignedRotationNew` action labels (added в rule premises). Previous
   formulation `not (old_pk = new_pk)` была misleading — доказывала
   только что ключи различаются, не сам dual-signature invariant.
*/
lemma identity_rotation_atomic_dual_signature:
    "All A old_pk new_pk #i.
        IdentityRotated(A, old_pk, new_pk) @ #i
        ==>
        (Ex sig_old #j. SignedRotationOld(old_pk, sig_old) @ #j & #j = #i)
        & (Ex sig_new #k. SignedRotationNew(new_pk, sig_new) @ #k & #k = #i)
        & not (old_pk = new_pk)"

/*
   Lemma: revocation_terminal_state

   Однажды revoked device entry не может быть activated again. Это
   formalized через restriction RevocationTerminal выше: any
   DeviceActivated event for device_pk must precede any DeviceRevoked
   event для same device_pk.
*/
lemma revocation_terminal_state:
    "All target_pk identity_pk #r.
        DeviceRevoked(target_pk, identity_pk) @ #r
        ==>
        not (Ex Approver #a.
            DeviceActivated(Approver, target_pk) @ #a & #r < #a)"

/*
   Lemma: unwrap_requires_signed_request
   (PhD-deep session 2026-05-17 inline F-PHD-RETRO-3 NEW)

   Любой UnwrapGranted event предваряется явной валидной Ed25519-подписью
   от device_sk соответствующего этому device_pk. Adversary без device_sk
   не может trigger Sealed Server release of unwrap share для этого
   устройства, даже если KT entry для устройства активна.

   Это закрывает разрыв между моделью и реальным кодом, где
   `verify_signed_unwrap_request` обязателен (signed_request.rs §verify).
*/
lemma unwrap_requires_signed_request:
    "All device_pk identity_pk chat_id sig #i.
        UnwrapGranted(device_pk, identity_pk, <chat_id, sig>) @ #i
        ==>
        Ex #s. UnwrapRequestSignedByDevice(device_pk, chat_id, sig) @ #s
        & #s = #i"

/*
   Lemma: unwrap_binds_chat_id_to_identity
   (PhD-deep session 2026-05-17 inline F-PHD-RETRO-3 NEW)

   Любой UnwrapGranted event связан с конкретной парой (device_pk, identity_pk)
   и chat_id входит в signed_request, поэтому одна и та же подпись не может
   быть переиспользована для другого chat_id либо другого identity_pk.

   Cross-account replay defence: adversary с corrupted device_X из identity_A
   не может проигрывать SignedUnwrapRequest, выпущенный для chat_A, против
   sealed-server endpoint identity_B's chat_B — chat_id и identity_pk оба
   входят в `unwrap_msg` подписи, поэтому verify провалится либо canonical
   bytes не совпадут.
*/
lemma unwrap_binds_chat_id_to_identity:
    "All device_pk identity_pk chat_id #i.
        UnwrapBoundToChat(device_pk, identity_pk, chat_id) @ #i
        ==>
        (Ex Approver #a.
            DeviceActivated(Approver, device_pk) @ #a & #a < #i)"

/*
   Lemma: twentyfour_words_leak_alone_strengthened
   (PhD-deep session 2026-05-17 inline F-PHD-RETRO-3 NEW — усиление через F-PHD-RETRO-3 fix)

   Strengthened статус по сравнению с `twentyfour_words_leak_alone_insufficient`:
   теперь модель явно доказывает что adversary с leaked identity_sk не может
   trigger UnwrapGranted ни для какого device, не имея device_sk этого
   устройства. Усиление возможно благодаря добавлению `!DeviceSk($D, device_sk)`
   premise в `sealed_server_unwrap`.
*/
lemma twentyfour_words_leak_alone_strengthened:
    "All A device_pk identity_pk chat_id sig #i #r.
        UnwrapGranted(device_pk, identity_pk, <chat_id, sig>) @ #i
        & Reveal24Words(A, identity_pk) @ #r
        ==>
        UnwrapRequestSignedByDevice(device_pk, chat_id, sig) @ #i"

/*
   Lemma: honest_setup_executable (exists-trace)

   Sanity: honest bootstrap + add second device via approval flow + Sealed
   Server unwrap для second device может выполниться без adversarial events.
*/
lemma honest_setup_executable: exists-trace
    "Ex A sk1 sk2 device2_pk identity_pk chat_id sig #i #j #k.
        BootstrapIdentity(A, sk1, sk2) @ #i
        & DeviceActivated(A, device2_pk) @ #j
        & UnwrapGranted(device2_pk, identity_pk, <chat_id, sig>) @ #k
        & i < j & j < k
        & (not Ex B id_sk #r. Reveal24Words(B, id_sk) @ #r)"

end
